Nacho Cheese Sauce

- 275 g colby jack (or other) cheese
Shred or grate cheese.

- 150 g lager beer (or water, ginger ale, cola, etc.)
- 10 g sodium citrate
Heat beer in a small saucepan. Stir in sodium citrate until dissolved.

When the liquid just comes to a bare simmer, start adding a little shredded cheese. Whisk until cheese is fully melted and combined. Repeat, a little at a time, until all cheese is mixed in.

- 1/4 tsp cayenne
Stir in cayenne.


